Class ProbabilisticPlaceField

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hswgt.teachingbox.core.rl.network.NetworkNode
      • org.hswgt.teachingbox.core.rl.network.rbf.RadialBasisFunction
        • org.hswgt.teachingbox.core.rl.network.networknodes.ProbabilisticPlaceField
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Copyable<NetworkNode>

    public class ProbabilisticPlaceField
extends RadialBasisFunction
implements Serializable
    Similar to a RadialBasisFunction with the difference that the computed value is used as a probability of switching the ProbabilisticPlaceField on/off. So a ProbabilisticPlaceField is a probabilistic binary feature.
